race.comment: WINNING TOAST (4) resumes in an open race having done some nice things last time in, winning a couple on the Ballarat Synthetic dominantly before measuring up fairly well in a good race at Flemington. Willing to forgive the run in the Silver Bowl Series Final when coming to the end of the campaign in a much stronger affair. Winkers go on and this BM62 looks very attainable if wound up. DANZSIN (11) is coming off a dominant four-length maiden win here last time out on heavy ground. No doubt that testing ground may have flattered him but he's on the up and has to be respected again. HE'S GODSPEED (3) has been good in two runs back from a spell, strong to the line at Coleraine last time out. Should be ready to peak now and can sit closer from the inside gate. MATROOSHI (10) gets up to 1400m again which should really suit. Her form at the trip in isolation reads quite well.
